spanishExample: No quiero que regreses, ve a estar con los demás.
englishTranslation: I don’t want you to come back, go be with the others.

spanishExample: Cuando regrese, no estaré de pie.
englishTranslation: When I come back, I won’t be standing.

spanishExample: Regresamos a casa y anduvimos mucho tiempo.
englishTranslation: We came back home and we walked a long time.

spanishExample: Todo hombre anda de manera diferente.
englishTranslation: Every man walks in a different way.

spanishExample: Andas rápido, pero ellos no andan mucho.
englishTranslation: You walk fast, but they don’t walk much.

spanishExample: Andaban bien.
englishTranslation: They were getting along fine.

spanishExample: ¡Regresa y habla con él!
englishTranslation: Come back and talk to him!

spanishExample: El gobierno no sabe nada de ello.
englishTranslation: The government doesn’t know anything about it.

spanishExample: Quiero que regrese con su cámara.
englishTranslation: I want him to come back with his camera.

spanishExample: ¡Regresen a casa! El papel está ahí.
englishTranslation: (Plural) Go back home! The paper is there.

spanishExample: Nos gusta el juego, entonces regresamos a jugar con él.
englishTranslation: We like the game, so we came back to play with it.

spanishExample: Él puede regresar a pie.
englishTranslation: He can come back by foot.

spanishExample: Anduve mucho tiempo tratando de encontrar este regalo.
englishTranslation: I walked a long time trying to find this gift.

spanishExample: ¡No regreses! Cualquiera puede hacer tu trabajo.
englishTranslation: Don’t come back! Anyone can do your job.

spanishExample: Él le regresará la carta.
englishTranslation: He will give her back the letter.

spanishExample: Regresemos ambos teléfonos.
englishTranslation: Let’s return both phones.

spanishExample: Puedes andar si regresas.
englishTranslation: You can walk if you go back.

spanishExample: Regresó la espada porque no le gustó.
englishTranslation: He gave the sword back because he didn’t like it.

spanishExample: No me regresaste mi tarjeta.
englishTranslation: You didn’t give me back my card.

spanishExample: Andaba por esa casa en la que tú andabas.
englishTranslation: I was walking by that house in which you were walking.

spanishExample: Anda ahí y diles que regresen.
englishTranslation: Walk there and tell them to come back.

spanishExample: Les regresaré la carne porque no es buena.
englishTranslation: I’ll give them back the meat because it’s not good.

spanishExample: Anduviste demasiado y por eso has regresado.
englishTranslation: You walked too much and that’s why you have returned.

spanishExample: Siempre regreso a las 6, pero hoy regresé a las 5.
englishTranslation: I always come back at 6, but today I came back at 5.

spanishExample: ¡Regrese! Podemos seguir andando.
englishTranslation: (Formal) Come back! We can keep walking.

spanishExample: Después de eso anduvieron tristes.
englishTranslation: After that they were(andar) sad.

spanishExample: No anduvo ese día.
englishTranslation: She didn’t walk that day.

spanishExample: Él siempre andaba cuando nosotros andábamos.
englishTranslation: He always walked when we were walking.
